Padre-Plugin-Template
=====================

Create new documents from a list of user defined templates. Optionally, 
the template may be processed with an external command prior to creating 
the new document.


INSTALLATION
============

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION
=========================

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Padre::Plugin::Template

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Padre-Plugin-Template

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Padre-Plugin-Template

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Padre-Plugin-Template

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Padre-Plugin-Template/


